  "description": [
    "KOREA AND THE KOREANS THE PASSING HERMIT KINGDOM ITS PEOPLE AND ITS HISTORY Land of Mornins Frehne With History Datlns Further Back Than the Beginning of the Christian Era This is the story of Korea the land that in these days is being swiftly and surely swallowed up by Japan Two years ago at the annual Newyears reception at the White House in Washington the strangest figures in all the gorgeous throng of foreign diplomats were two sad eyed mel ancholy men whose queer stiff polished hats distinguished them from the Chinese though their silk robes and their soft wadded slippers gave them otherwise a general resemblance They were the representatives of the Korean legation They stood apart in the great oast room after they had passed up the line to the president and they seemed to be mere onlookers with soma sad inter est in the gay spectacle They had rea son to be sad if sad they were It was the last Newyears day on which diplo matic representatives of Korea as a free nation would ever stand in the White House and greet the president of the groat republic Already the cloud was drawing over their country"
  ],
